    {
      "text": "A 23-year-old G1P0 woman at 14 weeks’ gestation presents to the clinic with new lumps on her areolas noticed over the past week. She reports no nipple discharge or breast pain. The lumps are small, soft, non-tender, and flesh-colored, with no signs of inflammation, scaling, or ulceration. She is anxious about the possibility of harm.\nWhich of the following is the most appropriate next step in management?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Topical antibiotics for suspected infection"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Immediate surgical excision"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Bilateral mammography and core needle biopsy"
        },
        {
          "id": 4,
          "text": "Reassurance that these lumps are normal pregnancy changes"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 4,
      "solution": "<div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>A) INCORRECT:</h4>The described lesions lack signs of infection, such as <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=_405NT&anker=Z2402afe504766ef84f64acad4aaea47b\" data-learningcard-id=\"_405NT\" data-anker=\"Z2402afe504766ef84f64acad4aaea47b\" data-section-id=\"0vXeA-\" data-sememe-id=\"3wYSir\">erythema</a>, warmth, or <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=qh0CUf&anker=Zfdfb82d83e675513c49619bc646fd20c\" data-learningcard-id=\"qh0CUf\" data-anker=\"Zfdfb82d83e675513c49619bc646fd20c\" data-section-id=\"PFcWRV0\" data-sememe-id=\"vIYAeq\">purulent</a> discharge. In <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=dO0orT&anker=Zeba6f488931dd463917047bb9c5f18f4\" data-learningcard-id=\"dO0orT\" data-anker=\"Zeba6f488931dd463917047bb9c5f18f4\" data-sememe-id=\"MM0M6g\">pregnancy</a>, benign changes like prominent Montgomery glands are common and not infectious. Topical <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mm0VTg&anker=Z4660f53b2b0c85aa3f9ab01bdf3f14f3\" data-learningcard-id=\"mm0VTg\" data-anker=\"Z4660f53b2b0c85aa3f9ab01bdf3f14f3\">antibiotics</a> are inappropriate without evidence of infection.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>B) INCORRECT:</h4>The lesions are small, soft, non-tender, and flesh-colored, suggesting benign changes rather than <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=WM0Png&anker=Z8c3bce39ca977e0f872b6d9fb3be8cfb\" data-learningcard-id=\"WM0Png\" data-anker=\"Z8c3bce39ca977e0f872b6d9fb3be8cfb\" data-section-id=\"azXQr00\" data-sememe-id=\"OHXIqz\">malignancy</a>. Surgical excision is reserved for suspicious or symptomatic lesions. The absence of concerning features makes <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=7I04Vh&anker=Za68e01313423572283ce418087f356cb\" data-learningcard-id=\"7I04Vh\" data-anker=\"Za68e01313423572283ce418087f356cb\" data-section-id=\"w41hlS0\">surgery</a> unnecessary and potentially harmful.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>C) INCORRECT:</h4>In a 23-year-old pregnant woman with benign-appearing areolar lesions, <span data-sememe-id=\"2faTlP\">mammography</span> and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=dP0odT&anker=Z57df09a239a55631c33266faef7f7331\" data-learningcard-id=\"dP0odT\" data-anker=\"Z57df09a239a55631c33266faef7f7331\" data-section-id=\"-tXDT-\" data-sememe-id=\"sSbtat\">core needle biopsy</a> are unnecessary. <span data-sememe-id=\"2faTlP\">Mammography</span> exposes the fetus to radiation, and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=dP0odT&anker=Z57df09a239a55631c33266faef7f7331\" data-learningcard-id=\"dP0odT\" data-anker=\"Z57df09a239a55631c33266faef7f7331\" data-section-id=\"-tXDT-\" data-sememe-id=\"sSbtat\">core needle biopsy</a> is reserved for suspicious lesions. The clinical presentation suggests benign <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=dO0orT&anker=Zeba6f488931dd463917047bb9c5f18f4\" data-learningcard-id=\"dO0orT\" data-anker=\"Zeba6f488931dd463917047bb9c5f18f4\" data-sememe-id=\"MM0M6g\">pregnancy</a>-related changes, not <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=WM0Png&anker=Z8c3bce39ca977e0f872b6d9fb3be8cfb\" data-learningcard-id=\"WM0Png\" data-anker=\"Z8c3bce39ca977e0f872b6d9fb3be8cfb\" data-section-id=\"azXQr00\" data-sememe-id=\"OHXIqz\">malignancy</a>.</div><div><h4 style='color: #34d399; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>D) CORRECT:</h4>Montgomery follicles are <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=W60PPS&anker=Z0881e9e2b0c86d7a0a62be5a7d5212e4\" data-learningcard-id=\"W60PPS\" data-anker=\"Z0881e9e2b0c86d7a0a62be5a7d5212e4\" data-section-id=\"ptcLeV0\" data-sememe-id=\"HdXKrC\">sebaceous glands</a> on the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=B60zMS&anker=Zc5ca0aafc6f59d77c93e2c57c876f7d2\" data-learningcard-id=\"B60zMS\" data-anker=\"Zc5ca0aafc6f59d77c93e2c57c876f7d2\" data-section-id=\"eEcxuV0\" data-sememe-id=\"CPXqSy\">areola</a> that become more prominent during <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=dO0orT&anker=Zeba6f488931dd463917047bb9c5f18f4\" data-learningcard-id=\"dO0orT\" data-anker=\"Zeba6f488931dd463917047bb9c5f18f4\" data-sememe-id=\"MM0M6g\">pregnancy</a> due to hormonal changes. They appear as small, soft, flesh-colored <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=_405NT&anker=Ze562e7aa25e368f0be0c7066c00f0243\" data-learningcard-id=\"_405NT\" data-anker=\"Ze562e7aa25e368f0be0c7066c00f0243\" data-section-id=\"-EXDy-\" data-sememe-id=\"YdXnoC\">nodules</a> without inflammation or tenderness. This increased visibility is due to elevated <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=uk0ppT&anker=Z9f773b700d306dca5a1f7c25325b2ece\" data-learningcard-id=\"uk0ppT\" data-anker=\"Z9f773b700d306dca5a1f7c25325b2ece\" data-section-id=\"dDXoWZ0\" data-sememe-id=\"OTbIIG\">estrogen</a> and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=uk0ppT&anker=Zf885481311d66b6abb1510c2c20cd63d\" data-learningcard-id=\"uk0ppT\" data-anker=\"Zf885481311d66b6abb1510c2c20cd63d\" data-section-id=\"SK1yf30\" data-sememe-id=\"2gXTux\">progesterone</a> levels, which enhance glandular differentiation and blood flow. Recognizing these changes as normal physiological adaptations prevents unnecessary diagnostic procedures or treatments.<br><br><span class=\"wichtig\"><b>Key learning point: </b></span>Montgomery follicles are <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=W60PPS&anker=Z0881e9e2b0c86d7a0a62be5a7d5212e4\" data-learningcard-id=\"W60PPS\" data-anker=\"Z0881e9e2b0c86d7a0a62be5a7d5212e4\" data-section-id=\"ptcLeV0\" data-sememe-id=\"HdXKrC\">sebaceous glands</a> in the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=B60zMS&anker=Zc5ca0aafc6f59d77c93e2c57c876f7d2\" data-learningcard-id=\"B60zMS\" data-anker=\"Zc5ca0aafc6f59d77c93e2c57c876f7d2\" data-section-id=\"eEcxuV0\" data-sememe-id=\"CPXqSy\">areola</a> that can become more prominent during <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=dO0orT&anker=Zeba6f488931dd463917047bb9c5f18f4\" data-learningcard-id=\"dO0orT\" data-anker=\"Zeba6f488931dd463917047bb9c5f18f4\" data-sememe-id=\"MM0M6g\">pregnancy</a>, presenting as small, soft, non-tender lumps.</div>",
